            <div class="welovestackoverflow" style="margin-top: 10px;">
                <div style="float: left;">
                        <p>
Vertex shaders are executable programs that execute as part of the programmable geometry pipeline in modern graphics APIs such as e.g. Direct3D or OpenGL. Vertex shaders are usually hardware accelerated on consumer hardware nowadays. The vertex shader processes one vertex at a time, followed by ...                         </p>
                                            <p style="margin-bottom: 0;">
                            <a title="tag wiki" href="/tags/vertex-shader/info">learn more&hellip;</a>
                            <span class="lsep">|</span> 
                            <a title="top answerers and askers in this tag" href="/tags/vertex-shader/topusers">top users</a> 
                            <span class="lsep">|</span> 
                            <a title="common, alternate spellings or phrasings for this tag" href="/tags/vertex-shader/synonyms">synonyms</a>
                                                    </p>
                </div>
